    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The desire for amusement, instead of being quenched and arbitrarily ruled down, should be controlled and directed by painstaking effort upon the part of the parents. Their desire to make gifts may be turned into pure and holy channels and made to result in good to our fellow men by supplying the treasury in the great, grand work for which Christ came into our world. Self-denial and self-sacrifice marked His course of action. Let it mark ours who profess to love Jesus because in Him is centered our hope of eternal life.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 12-9-1884\" data-link=\"821.6072\">Ibid</span>.</span></a></sup>",
