    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The tree may be as tall and its branches as wide as shall best suit the occasion; but let its boughs be laden with the golden and silver fruit of your beneficence, and present this to Him as your Christmas gift. Let your donations be sanctified by prayer.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 12-11-1879\" data-link=\"821.3076\">The Review and Herald, December 11, 1879</span>.</span></a></sup>",
